# tourbillon / backups orchestration on kodiak.
#
# After ADR-004 (kodiak-side service user), the A2 cron entries (repos sync,
# hosts sync) moved to the tourbillon user's crontab. What's left on ldavis
# is monitoring — saratoga DR replication freshness checks + monthly host
# restore drills + the weekly summary heartbeat.
#
# Every entry except weekly-summary.sh runs through bin/mail-on-output.sh,
# which gives the email a meaningful Subject line (e.g. "kodiak: saratoga
# check FAILED (exit 1)") instead of cron's default "Cron <ldavis@kodiak>
# <script-path> ..." which is unreadable next to the weekly-summary subject.
#
# weekly-summary.sh self-mails (it's an unconditional weekly send, not
# triggered by output), so it's NOT wrapped — would double-send.
#
# MAILTO is left set for belt-and-suspenders: if a cron entry somehow
# bypasses mail-on-output.sh and produces output, cron's own mail still
# fires. The wrapper handles the common path.
MAILTO=lynchdavis0@gmail.com

# Daily 08:00 — alert if saratoga's ZFS replication hasn't landed a fresh
# snapshot in the last 26h. Silent on success.
0 8 * * * /home/ldavis/development/server-backups/bin/mail-on-output.sh "saratoga check" /home/ldavis/development/server-backups/tests/check-saratoga-replication.sh

# Monthly restore-drill — verifies backup integrity for each host
# end-to-end (mirror hash == source hash == reverse-rsync'd hash).
# Silent on success. Add one line per host as the fleet grows.
30 6 1 * * /home/ldavis/development/server-backups/bin/mail-on-output.sh "restore drill arrow-iii" /home/ldavis/development/server-backups/tests/restore-drill.sh arrow-iii
35 6 1 * * /home/ldavis/development/server-backups/bin/mail-on-output.sh "restore drill pilatus" /home/ldavis/development/server-backups/tests/restore-drill.sh pilatus

# Weekly summary — Sunday 08:00. Self-mails via msmtp with a useful
# Subject line ("kodiak weekly backup summary YYYY-MM-DD"). NOT wrapped
# (would double-send). Acts as a heartbeat: if no email arrives some
# Sunday, monitoring itself is broken.
0 8 * * 0 /home/ldavis/development/server-backups/bin/weekly-summary.sh
